1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,092
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:04,092 --> 00:00:07,163
[Episode Twenty-five]

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,640
Today we are talking about ancient Chinese philosophy.

4
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:12,560
It is a question discussed by the academic circles.

5
00:00:11,199 --> 00:00:13,368
[Hu Shi, styled Shizhi, Professor at Peking University]

6
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:15,200
What you said just now is a political issue,

7
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:16,880
a matter of political discussion.

8
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,240
As a student,

9
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,640
it's good to take an interest in Shandong's problems.

10
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,240
But can Shandong be returned to China?

11
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:27,040
This was the issue discussed, studied, and decided

12
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,040
by the statesmen of the Paris Peace Conference,

13
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:31,360
and not an issue that we can decide

14
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:32,960
in the classroom today.

15
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,800
But students believe that it is impossible

16
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:36,240
to completely separate academics and politics.

17
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:38,720
As the saying goes, there is no egg under the overturned nest.

18
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:41,200
If a country can't even protect its sovereignty,

19
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,680
what's the point of learning?

20
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:45,280
Exactly.

21
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,680
Isn't this disturbing the classroom order?

22
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,600
Academic and political issues

23
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:52,640
really shouldn't be confused.

24
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:54,880
There is no egg under the overturned nest.

25
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:01,760
Students, please be quiet.

26
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:03,520
Students!

27
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,320
Quiet please.

28
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:10,400
Student Guo Xingang.

29
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:11,440
You are in class today,

30
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,520
talking endlessly about Shandong's problems.

31
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,040
Do you find that useful?

32
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:17,360
The decision on Shandong lies with Wilson.

33
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:19,120
Not with one of the students.

34
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,520
The students' task is to learn.

35
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,440
To learn that the best state of mind

36
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,120
is a peaceful mind,

37
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,120
instead of having a deer in your heart.

38
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:29,040
Sir,

39
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,520
there are not many university students in China.

40
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,680
Even if we don't care about the Shandong issue,

41
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,120
Wilson is a foreigner,

42
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,880
why should he care about our Shandong?

43
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,480
To tie the sovereignty of Shandong

44
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,160
to a foreigner's mouth,

45
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,600
students cannot accept that.

46
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:43,200
Excuse me, sir.

47
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:47,040
I can't stay calm.

48
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,880
As students, we should concentrate on our studies.

49
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,560
I think Guo is right. Yes.

50
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:53,680
Wilson is a foreigner,

51
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,120
why should he care about our Shandong?

52
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,160
We should care about ourselves.

53
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,200
Time to eat!

54
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,640
Okay, right away.

55
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,400
Time to eat!

56
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,400
Time to eat.

57
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:04,720
Okay.

58
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,440
How is it steamed cornbread again?

59
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:10,880
I have to show movies tonight.

60
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,840
I can't run on this.

61
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,120
I can make abalone and sea cucumber.

62
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,160
Can you afford that?

63
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:15,520
These days,

64
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,520
in addition to the dozen people in the group,

65
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,960
there are no guests at all.

66
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,160
Did I make this steamed cornbread

67
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,680
or borrow it from outside?

68
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,880
Don't you like to eat?

69
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:25,680
Comrade Yu Shewei,

70
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,840
why are we just eating steamed cornbread here?

71
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,680
Where are the other comrades?

72
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,680
Just as I was preparing for the evening meeting

73
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:32,640
telling everyone about it.

74
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,400
Ge Xiumei from our screening group

75
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,600
has retired from the club,

76
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,920
leaving a letter, and has returned to Tianjin today.

77
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:40,400
How can there be so many quitters in only one month?

78
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,640
Then there are a few comrades

79
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,760
who will not also quit the club, right?

80
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,440
Guo is busy with the petition group.

81
00:02:44,113 --> 00:02:46,836
[Chen Yannian, eldest son of Chen Duxiu]

82
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,000
Bai Lan will not come back when she goes out as a tutor.

83
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,600
Distribute these.

84
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:49,840
Okay.

85
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,960
I think our mutual aid society should be reorganized.

86
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,240
Regarding this petition group,

87
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,920
I think it's more important than our mutual aid society.

88
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,840
You can eat out when you go out to work.

89
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,000
When the family comes, they can go out and enjoy it.

90
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,840
Is this still communism?

91
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,000
When joining the society, didn't we agree

92
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,680
to share weal and woe as a family?

93
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,160
How come there are privileges and differences now?

94
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,080
The most critical question now

95
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,360
is to make money.

96
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,240
Since we started the club, we have been unable to make ends meet.

97
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,480
Now we're running out of money.

98
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,880
I agree with Comrade Yannian.

99
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,320
The biggest problem we face now

100
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,280
is the problem of survival.

101
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,040
Three work-study groups

102
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,040
have to come up with a better way.

103
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,240
Brother Guo said

104
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,240
to let them come to our place to package meals.

105
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,800
and "New Youth" magazine revenue

106
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:33,840
has also come down.

107
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,280
It's all confiscated.

108
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:38,480
This comrade Guo Xingang is sick and tired at ordinary times.

109
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,480
Not active in group activities.

110
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:43,120
The mention of Qingdao is like having chicken blood.

111
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,880
What does he care about chicken blood and cow blood?

112
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,560
Having an income is the key.

113
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:49,120
If you don't earn money, you won't be able to eat.

114
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,480
I'm a chef.

115
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,080
It's time to wash and sleep.

116
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,080
I have discussed everything with Comrade Yi.

117
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,840
Go to their school tomorrow to find the clerk.

118
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,760
Give him ten percent more commission.

119
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,360
See if he can help us get some business.

120
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,880
This is unfair competition.

121
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,480
It's survival of the fittest.

122
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,680
Don't care so much.

123
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,360
Then I'll go with you tomorrow.

124
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,280
If it were not for Xie Wanying

125
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,560
mobilizing girls from all schools

126
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,520
to give us charity,

127
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,280
our screening group would have closed down.

128
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,960
I can't stand being a seven-foot man.

129
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,160
Yannian,

130
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,920
I think we need to find a time

131
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:17,600
to discuss the articles of association.

132
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:18,960
Okay, I think it's very important.

133
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:19,920
That's let's do it.

134
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:22,400
Go on.

135
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,120
Brother Mao,

136
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,080
I haven't seen you for so long.

137
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,600
We all thought you were back in Hunan.

138
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,200
Actually, it's been half a month,

139
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,400
and I've did two things.

140
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:31,680
What's the first?

141
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,280
With the help of Mr. Zhang Shizhao

142
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,240
that we sent the first batch of students

143
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,600
from our Hunan to France.

144
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:36,720
The second thing,

145
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,240
was following Mr. Li Dazhao

146
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,840
to Changxindian several times.

147
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,160
Every day, coming home at night.

148
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,440
I really don't have time to see you.

149
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,760
I said I haven't seen you for half a month.

150
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,200
Why do you look tired?

151
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,200
Actually,

152
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,480
I'm here for one more thing.

153
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,920
I'm leaving tomorrow,

154
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,120
back to Hunan.

155
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:54,800
You're going back?

156
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:55,440
Yes.

157
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,720
In the blink of an eye, more than half a year.

158
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,160
Things in Beijing have been settled.

159
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,680
But what about the Xinmin Society?

160
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,880
There are still many things to deal with.

161
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,160
During my time in Beijing,

162
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,840
I am very grateful to your brothers for taking care of me.

163
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:04,960
So I still

164
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,320
want to specially

165
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,920
politely decline.

166
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,040
Brother Runzhi,

167
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,240
that's so kind of you.

168
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,840
It's rare to get to know you.

169
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:13,760
And from your viewpoint,

170
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,560
I can see something that I can't see in Beijing.

171
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,040
How do you say this?

172
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:20,960
I don't know exactly.

173
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,040
I always feel that only you

174
00:05:23,402 --> 00:05:26,103
[Mao Zedong, styled Runzhi, Peking University Library Assistant]

175
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,040
can see what is really happening

176
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,400
to the people.

177
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,160
Actually,

178
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,520
I should thank you both.

179
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:32,240
Look,

180
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:34,080
you guys are working to support yourselves.

181
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:34,880
This

182
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,240
is a practical approach to the public.

183
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,400
But we continue to do it anymore.

184
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:39,920
We are going to fail.

185
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,320
Qiaonian, come.

186
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,040
I think

187
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,880
failure is not so terrible.

188
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,480
Why not start all over again?

189
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,360
Maybe

190
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,960
we can find a new road again.

191
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,000
Isn't that right, Yannian?

192
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,160
This mutual aid society has been running for almost two months.

193
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,680
I always feel that there is something missing.

194
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,760
It seems to have only one shell and no soul.

195
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,560
This road still won't work.

196
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,800
I wish to cross the Yellow River,

197
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,160
yet ice blocks the river.

198
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,480
I wish to climb Taihang,

199
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,080
yet snow covers the mountain.

200
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,720
Hard is the journey.

201
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,040
Hard is the journey.

202
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,600
Many roads divided,

203
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,200
which to take?

204
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:22,240
Yannian,

205
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,280
Qiaonian.

206
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,640
I think,

207
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:25,760
although the road is long,

208
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,960
but Beijing

209
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,400
has a kingly spirit.

210
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,680
Mr. Zhongfu,

211
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:30,800
Mr. Shouchang,

212
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:31,760
their claims

213
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,440
are a deafening,

214
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,120
kingly energy that cleanses the heaven and earth,

215
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,400
and

216
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,080
they are also the spiritual leaders and mentors

217
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,520
of our new youth.

218
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,120
And the new youth of our time

219
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:44,000
is to connect this kingly spirit with the earthly spirit.

220
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:45,600
In practice,

221
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,880
searching up and down

222
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:48,720
for a new way out

223
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,000
for the world.

224
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:51,920
Each age brings forth

225
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,320
a new genius on this noble land.

226
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:55,360
Their poems and articles will be known for ages to come.

227
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:56,400
Brother Runzhi,

228
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,920
to save the country and the people,

229
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,760
I am willing to walk with you,

230
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,440
to work together,

231
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,760
to cheer together.

232
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,680
A long wind

233
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:06,800
will break the waves.

234
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,680
Setting sail

235
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,360
and crossing the sea.

236
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:17,920
Encourage each other!

237
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:24,640
Runzhi,

238
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,240
you're going back this time,

239
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,440
what are you going to do?

240
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,400
I want to know our China well

241
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,720
and see what our country lacks.

242
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,840
I can give you the answer to your question right now.

243
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,680
Science and democracy.

244
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,920
What China lacks most now

245
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:40,880
are these two things.

246
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:42,400
Well said, sir.

247
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,200
Precisely said.

248
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:44,560
But,

249
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,320
I still want to know about it.

250
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,160
A country like ours,

251
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,920
where most of the people are farmers and illiterate.

252
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,040
What is it like?

253
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:51,840
Only then

254
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,160
can we walk the path where science and democracy converge.

255
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,080
That's a good question.

256
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,040
Asked well.

257
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,120
I recently wrote an article.

258
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,640
on "Youth and the Countryside".

259
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,640
I'm also trying to explore this question.

260
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,000
Young people dare to think and do.

261
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:04,800
Worth advocating.

262
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,240
China's development

263
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,240
must be supported by the introduction

264
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,520
of the most advanced theories.

265
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:11,840
Yes, sir.

266
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:14,480
Sir,

267
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,920
I have a question

268
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,040
I've always wanted to ask you.

269
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:17,920
Go on.

270
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,520
Do you really think

271
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,960
the fundamental problem of China

272
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,520
is a problem of backward cultural traditions?

273
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:25,360
No.

274
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,040
It is not culture that lags China behind.

275
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:30,400
It's the lack of theories to guide the sustainable development of society.

276
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,433
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Dean of Liberal Arts at Peking University]

277
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:31,680
Scientific theories.

278
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,200
Then why did you two gentlemen

279
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,720
use so much energy

280
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:36,000
shaking down old culture?

281
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,560
Because it suppresses and hinders

282
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,160
the birth of science and democracy.

