00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,680
Here, steamed buns.

562
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,640
There are no Anhui dishes today.

563
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:53,440
No Shandong cuisine.

564
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:54,720
Only dumplings.

565
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,720
Okay, just dumplings.

566
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,960
What about today?

567
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:02,080
Let's have a chat with these dumplings.

568
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:03,120
Alright?

569
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:03,680
Okay, sit down.

570
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,040
Yu Xiusong, you start first.

571
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,000
Everybody sit down.

572
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,280
Sit down.

573
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,320
Dear Mr. Cai.

574
00:23:16,823 --> 00:23:18,155
[Cai Yuanpei, styled Jiemin, President of Peking University]

575
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,240
Dear mentors.

576
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:19,600
Dear ladies.

577
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:21,600
Dear comrades.

578
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,040
Today

579
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,480
was supposed to be a sad day for the members

580
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:26,560
of our work-study mutual aid society.

581
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:28,880
But because of Mr. Cai

582
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,560
and the arrival of the mentors,

583
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,880
it has become a memorable day again.

584
00:23:33,758 --> 00:23:36,472
[Lu Xun, Civil servant under the Ministry of Education]

585
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,120
More than two months ago,

586
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,120
with the support and sponsorship of our mentors,

587
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,560
we started this work-study mutual aid society

588
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:40,480
and our members

589
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,600
are all

590
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:43,200
young men and women around 20 years old.

591
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:45,360
This is our first step towards life

592
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,520
is also the experience and pursuit

593
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:48,640
of our ideal life.

594
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,960
We persisted for more than two months.

595
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:52,800
We failed today.

596
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,640
We can't thank our mentors enough

597
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:55,680
for their support and teaching.

598
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,560
Let's ask Mr. Cai to give us a lecture.

599
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:04,800
Please sit down.

600
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,640
I'm sorry.

601
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:13,440
There's been a lot going on at school these months.

602
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,280
I didn't care

603
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:17,120
about the work-study mutual aid society.

604
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:19,520
I was surprised to hear

605
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:22,320
that it was going to be disbanded.

606
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,880
I ran to see everyone.

607
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:28,160
I am concerned about the theory of mutual aid

608
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:30,960
and you are practicing it

609
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,560
with your own actions.

610
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,560
So you all are a lot better than me,

611
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:36,320
although in front of you,

612
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,240
I am the head of a school.

613
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:39,600
In this respect,

614
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,600
I want to learn from you.

615
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:45,760
I salute you young people

616
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:46,960
for your bravery.

617
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,000
I believe

618
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:51,040
your practice and experiment of mutual aid theory today

619
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,400
will become a valuable asset in your life.

620
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:06,480
I thank you sir for your approval and encouragement.

621
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:07,840
In the past two months,

622
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:09,920
we have tried our best

623
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:10,720
to do everything we can.

624
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,240
The experiment failed

625
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:13,920
but we have a clear conscience.

626
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:15,920
Today I would like to take this opportunity

627
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,840
to ask the gentlemen.

628
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,120
In your opinion

629
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:20,880
what is the root cause

630
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:21,840
of the failure of this mutual aid society?

631
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:24,400
You're good.

632
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,640
Failure without discouragement.

633
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:30,080
Keep a clear head and actively look for reasons.

634
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,560
In order to have the courage to move forward in the future

635
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:33,520
Isn't it?

636
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:34,400
Yes.

637
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:38,480
Good. Student Yannian, let me ask you first.

638
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:41,600
What do you think is the root of this failure?

639
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,240
I think there must be more than one reason.

640
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,440
But perhaps the most important thing is

641
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,480
that we don't understand

642
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:49,440
the theory and practice of mutual aid enough,

643
00:25:50,080 --> 00:25:50,720
by either missing the point

644
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:51,920
or deviating from it.

645
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:55,920
What do you all think?

646
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,360
I think there are many disputes.

647
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,960
Brother Zhongfu, I suggest opening another column

648
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:08,320
for everyone

649
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,560
to properly summarize the experience and lessons learned.

650
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:11,760
What do you think?

651
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:14,960
Okay, Master Cai is right.

652
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:19,200
Then, on behalf of "New Youth",

653
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:23,680
I'll formally ask the members for a draft.

654
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:26,000
You have done a very useful experiment

655
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:28,800
for the youth of China.

656
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:31,040
Your summary and experience

657
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:32,560
is the most convincing.

658
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,160
At the same time,

659
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,960
I also want to ask Shouchang and Shizhi to write the manuscript.

660
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:37,920
Shizhi,

661
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,400
you tell everyone about your feelings.

662
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:46,720
I have studied work-study programmes.

663
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:48,720
In the United States,

664
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,800
tens of thousands of people live a work-study life.

665
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,360
But for young people in the United States

666
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,720
they are not interested in the work-study program.

667
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,080
They feel it is an extremely normal

668
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,600
and free choice.

669
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,680
It's not a great new life.

670
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,360
But in China,

671
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:03,200
it is an amazing thing.

672
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,560
As for us,

673
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:06,560
why did it fail after a few months?

674
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,240
There are many reasons.

675
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,280
I saw at least one of them.

676
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,440
It was not well planned.

677
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:15,840
Working more and studying less.

678
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,280
The result?

679
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,840
It's just that working is much more bitter.

680
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,640
The fun of studying is a little less.

681
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,640
Work-study.

682
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,080
Work. Study.

683
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,760
What is the relationship between the two?

684
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,680
Have you thought about it?

685
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,280
The purpose of working is to study.

686
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,880
And think about it.

687
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:38,000
Have we read many books in the past two months?

688
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:40,000
Do you have time to read?

689
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:41,680
Are there students

690
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,120
who have read less books than before

691
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,960
in the past two months?

692
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:47,920
There are.

693
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,880
So, our mutual aid society

694
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:52,800
has reversed the original intention.

695
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,280
How can it be successful?

696
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,400
It's not, Shizhi.

697
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,720
You are a well-fed man, but you don't know if a hungry man is hungry.

698
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:01,120
See?

699
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,720
This plaque has just been taken off.

700
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:06,960
Lu Xun writes very well.

701
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,920
To sweat on one's forehead,

702
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:12,080
than stain blood on one's hands.

703
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,080
Why do students do this experiment?

704
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,360
In order to rely on their own labor.

705
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:18,960
To maintain their studies.

706
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:19,760
Right?

707
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,680
So what's wrong with the students?

708
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:23,040
I don't think there's anything wrong with it.

709
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,960
Shizhi, what you just said.

710
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,840
With no work, how can I finish my studies?

711
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:30,080
And with what to eat?

712
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,160
Aren't you throwing cold water on everyone?

713
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,000
Why am I pouring cold water on it?

714
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,000
Shouchang, since you say so,

715
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:37,440
I'd like to hear your thoughts.

716
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:39,840
My opinion is this:

717
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,800
to find the root of the failure of our mutual aid society,

718
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,720
first of all, we must recognize clearly

719
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,480
whether it is due to internal

720
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:48,080
or external causes.

721
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:52,000
Yannian, have you considered

722
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,440
the deeper reason?

723
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:54,960
What do you mean?

724
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,760
I mean, have you ever thought about

725
00:28:58,080 --> 00:29:00,560
there is something wrong with the theory of mutual aid itself.

726
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,480
You mean there is something wrong with the theory of mutual aid itself?

727
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:03,520
Unscientific.

728
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:04,640
I think at least everyone

729
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:05,680
can study this problem.

730
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:07,280
There are two points.

731
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:08,480
First,

732
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,480
is the theory of mutual aid

733
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,840
a scientific theory?

734
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:13,600
Second,

735
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,760
is it suitable for China?

736
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,360
So what's your conclusion?

737
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:20,800
I think the success of the October Revolution in Russia

738
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,600
is more suitable for China than the theory of mutual aid.

739
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,120
Shouchang, you digress.

740
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:27,200
I think you are taking this opportunity

741
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,560
to promote the October Revolution

742
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,320
On this occasion,

743
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:32,000
it's not appropriate to talk about these things.

744
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,920
I disagree with you.

745
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:35,840
It's not, Shizhi.

746
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,800
I didn't take the opportunity to promote the October Revolution.

747
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:40,720
I'm just offering a new idea

748
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:41,840
for everyone to discuss.

749
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,200
You don't mention the October Revolution.

750
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:44,880
You're against it, right?

751
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:45,600
There is no objection.

752
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:46,880
No, then how is it not contradictory?

753
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,680
On such an occasion today-

754
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:48,400
Shizhi, I think it just contradicts-

755
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:49,360
All right, all right, all right.

756
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,480
I have my opinion.

757
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:52,000
Students have their own opinions.

758
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,600
Brother Shouchang, Professor Shizhi.

759
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,080
What you two said makes sense to me.

760
00:29:56,720 --> 00:30:00,480
Just don't discuss it here today.

761
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,400
Let's find a place another day

762
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,080
to have a good discussion.

763
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:04,640
Alright.

764
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:06,320
Come on.

765
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,160
Failure teaches success.

766
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:10,720
The end is the beginning.

767
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:12,960
Our task today

768
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,560
is to finish these buns.

769
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:16,480
Not just steamed buns

770
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:18,960
but also the pickles and garlic here all eaten,

771
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:21,600
until there is not a grain left in the clean canteen.

772
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,720
Come on.

773
00:30:29,125 --> 00:30:29,466
Here.

774
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:37,040
Brother Shouchang, I really didn't object.

775
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:38,080
You two, eat the buns.

776
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,280
I'm eating, Mr. Cai.

777
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:06,240
Do you really agree

778
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:08,000
to let them both go back to Shanghai?

779
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:15,360
Didn't you also read Liu Wenyao's letter?

780
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,760
It said that the places for work-study in France

781
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,600
were allocated to the French class of Aurora University,

782
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:22,160
and that the places in the French language training center in Beijing were finished.

783
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,160
If they want to go to France,

784
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,240
they have to go back to Shanghai to finish their studies

785
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:29,760
Obviously, he designed this in the morning.

786
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,600
These two boys really want

787
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:32,960
to go to France to work and study.

788
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,360
Then let them go back to Shanghai.

789
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:36,960
The mutual aid society failed.

790
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:38,880
It hit them both particularly hard.

791
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:40,640
Especially Yannian.

792
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:41,600
The child has a heavy heart.

793
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:43,600
I'm afraid he can't bear it.

794
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:48,320
These two children are now taking risks and struggling.

795
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,000
An indomitable time.

796
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:53,760
In particular, they needs hardship to be tempered.

797
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:55,520
Don't worry.

798
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:56,800
They have an old man like me.

799
00:31:57,520 --> 00:32:00,480
Will these two kids be demoralized?

800
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:05,360
Yannian, Qiaonian.

801
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:08,320
Come out. I want to talk to you.

802
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:12,800
Dad,

803
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:14,560
you have to lecture again.

804
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,800
No, I'm just talking to you.

805
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:24,880
You are going to Shanghai.

806
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:29,600
Go get a chair and sit down.

807
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:30,960
I lifted up my head and said I was tired.

808
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:44,320
Yannian,

809
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:48,320
the mutual aid experiment failed.

810
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,600
I want to ask you, are you still so convinced

811
00:32:52,480 --> 00:32:53,680
of the theory of anarchism?

812
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:56,960
Will you be angry if I say I firmly believe in it?

813
00:32:58,400 --> 00:32:58,960
I won't.

814
00:32:59,200 --> 00:32:59,920
Truth?

815
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:00,720
Truth.

816
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:01,920
Why?

817
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:04,160
Because I saw your reflection.

818
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,680
If you have reflection, you will not be blind.

819
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,280
I believe

820
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:12,960
you will surely find a right way.

821
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:16,560
I am willing to give you time.

822
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:21,040
I'm willing to go looking for it with you.

823
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:22,880
Thank you.

824
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:27,200
Dad, I thought you were going to force us again

825
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,640
to study the October Revolution.

826
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:30,000
I'm not forcing you,

827
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:32,240
just suggesting.

828
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:33,680
Rest assured,

829
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,680
we will stick to the theory of mutual aid,

830
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:36,960
but we will

831
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,800
learn from different perspectives.

832
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:40,800
Good.

833
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:50,800
During my stay in Beijing,

834
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:55,040
I have seen your growth with my own eyes.

835
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:56,320
To tell the truth,

836
00:33:57,520 --> 00:34:00,240
as a father, I am very pleased.

837
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,440
We also have a new understanding of you.

838
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:05,840
Your thoughts have also benefited me and Qiaonian a lot.

839
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:07,360
But there's just one thing.

840
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:09,920
What?

841
00:34:10,640 --> 00:34:11,520
It's nothing.

842
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,840
We hope you will change

843
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:18,160
your style and habits,

844
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:20,560
especially when you treat your colleagues.

845
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:22,640
That would hurt them too much.

846
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:38,400
I'll fry some peanuts for you.

847
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:39,520
Take it back to eat on the road.

848
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:51,520
What are you doing?

849
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:10,080
The two children are going to Shanghai.

850
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,320
Can't I fry peanuts for them?

851
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:35,680
Go and get some pumpkin seeds.

852
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:36,640
Why?

853
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:40,560
When Qiaonian was a child, he liked fried peanuts.

854
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:43,760
Yannian likes to eat pumpkin seeds.

855
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:58,480
Pumpkin seeds and peanuts are cooked differently.

856
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:00,000
You'll fry it if you stir it up.

857
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:06,560
When Yannian was young,

858
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:09,680
he liked to eat fried pumpkin seeds.

859
00:36:10,240 --> 00:36:11,280
You don't know this?

860
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,320
Think of this one?

861
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:30,240
It's a bit repetitive with what we published in the last issue.

862
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,200
So I suggest

863
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:31,920
this-

864
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:33,280
Shouchang, Zhongfu.

865
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:33,680
Shizhi.

866
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:34,960
Tell you some good news.

867
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,200
My teacher, Mr. Dewey, has decided

868
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,920
to come to China from Japan on the 27th to give lectures.

869
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,680
I'm here to ask for leave.

870
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:43,760
I want to meet my teacher in Shanghai.

871
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,840
I see you're happy.

872
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,200
The 27th is still a long way off.

873
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:48,960
Besides, at that time,

874
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:51,120
I should also step down as dean of liberal arts.

875
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:52,960
You don't have to ask me for leave.

876
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:54,320
What are you talking about?

877
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:56,240
You've always been my dean.

878
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:58,320
Dewey's coming to China is a good thing.

879
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:00,960
Although I don't fully agree with his

880
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,160
experimental viewpoint.

881
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:05,280
But his pragmatic ideas

882
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,720
are still refreshing.

883
00:37:06,960 --> 00:37:07,440
Shizhi,

884
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:11,200
you, Jiang Menglin, and Tao Xingzhi

885
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:12,720
are his disciples.

886
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,080
You guys plan well.

887
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,400
Let him stay in China for a few more days.

888
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:17,360
A couple more.

889
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:18,720
Now, Chinese people

890
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:21,520
have a good feeling for the United States and Wilson.

891
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:22,800
I told you,

892
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,880
we've been planning Mr. Dewey's trip

893
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,960
for more than a month.

894
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:29,760
I hope that my teacher's visit to China

895
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:31,840
will create a whirlwind

896
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,040
of experimentalism in China.

897
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:35,760
Because experimentalism is so useful to China,

898
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:36,960
China wants to be strong.

899
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,960
We must learn from the United States in its entirety.

900
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:40,560
Shizhi, that's biased.

901
00:37:41,040 --> 00:37:42,160
How long has the United States been founded?

902
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:44,000
How many years is China's history?

903
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:45,680
The national conditions of the two countries are different.

904
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:46,800
Cultural traditions are different.

905
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:48,160
How can it be compared?

906
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:50,800
I agree with Shouchang.

907
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,480
But today?

908
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:54,160
I'd rather hope that the United States

909
00:37:54,240 --> 00:37:55,840
can help us contain Japan.

910
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:57,840
So I wrote an article last month

911
00:37:58,320 --> 00:38:00,240
praising this Wilson as a great man.

912
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:02,560
You still think so?

913
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:05,200
Now I call him Big Cannon

914
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,640
Big Cannon? What do you mean?

915
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,160
He fired a gun.

916
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:11,920
It's not like you didn't read

917
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,120
his fourteen peace proposals

918
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,320
Which one is not an empty gun?

919
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,440
Let me see.

920
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,760
China pins Shandong problem on him.

921
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,200
Concerning.

922
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:21,280
I think you two are too pessimistic.

923
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:23,280
I hope the facts don't make us pessimistic.

924
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:27,360
Mr. Cai.

925
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:28,000
Everyone's here.

926
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:29,120
Sir.

927
00:38:29,360 --> 00:38:29,840
Mr. Cai.

928
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:31,120
Come on, sit down.

929
00:38:31,520 --> 00:38:32,240
Please sit down.

930
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:39,120
I have something to tell you three.

931
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:41,520
Wang Daxie told me today.

932
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:43,840
He said that the Paris Peace Conference was not going well.

933
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:46,240
Japan which presented two documents

934
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:47,840
at the Paris Peace Conference.

935
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:50,320
One is, Duan Qirui,

936
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:52,000
in order to borrow money from the Japanese,

937
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,120
admitted that Japan

938
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,280
could inherit all the German rights and interests in Shandong

939
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,560
under a secret treaty.

940
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,320
What about the second one?

941
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,840
It's Britain, France and other countries

942
00:39:02,160 --> 00:39:04,400
also acquiesced in such a treaty.

943
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:08,080
So now the Japanese are trying to force

944
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:09,840
the Americans into submission with these two documents.

945
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,240
So,

946
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:14,720
Wilson doesn't want this justice either.

947
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,280
Wang Daxie told me

948
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:19,760
the United States has always shared interests.

949
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:23,120
He must resist this request from Japan.

950
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:25,280
But to what extent can it be resisted?

951
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:26,720
It's hard to say.

952
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:28,640
Then Britain, France and Italy are unreliable.

953
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:32,560
The key is to look at this requirement of the United States for Japan.

954
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,560
What kind of plan will it come up with?

955
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:36,080
It's over.

956
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:38,240
Unreliable.

957
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,440
Who is unreliable?

958
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:40,800
I think Wilson is a gentleman.

959
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:42,160
Discussion is reliable.

960
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:43,520
Let's just leave it at that.

961
00:39:44,240 --> 00:39:46,000
Now we have to take care of ourselves.

962
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:47,680
If something really big like this happens,

963
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,040
What will we do at Peking University?

964
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:51,280
Now Peking University is famous.

965
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,680
Zhongfu and Shouchang as well.

966
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:55,680
You're all on the police department's list.

967
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:58,080
More importantly, our students don't attend classes.

968
00:39:58,480 --> 00:40:00,240
This heart can't be held back.

969
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:02,800
It's really the Paris Peace Conference that's going to go wrong.

970
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:05,440
That's bound to happen in China.

971
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:07,120
So I said,

972
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:11,520
brother Zhongfu, we have to plan ahead.

973
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:12,800
Mr. Cai,

974
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:14,720
I think the current situation

975
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:15,920
is a good situation.

976
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,360
Everyone's patriotic enthusiasm

977
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:18,640
is all mobilized.

978
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,240
We just take advantage of the situation.

979
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:22,480
Mr. Cai, I don't think we can mess around.

980
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,560
This is the principle of guiding the situation according to the situation.

981
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,960
Zhongfu, why don't you talk?

982
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,280
I have to think about it.

983
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:34,960
You really have to think about it this time.

984
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,120
You can't go to extremes anymore.

985
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,880
No, Shizhi, how come you've been spending so much time lately

986
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:44,720
always talking about extremes?

987
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:45,760
You don't pour cold water on everyone.

988
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:47,040
Do you feel uncomfortable?

989
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:48,160
I didn't mean that.

990
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:50,080
I'm just saying what I think.

991
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,680
No offense, brother Zhongfu.

992
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:57,280
I'm hungry. I'll be back to eat.

993
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,840
Is he angry?

994
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:04,640
Isn't that what it is?

995
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:06,960
Feudalism has grown up?

996
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:14,000
Mr. Cai,

997
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:15,440
I'm- I'm also hungry.

998
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:16,480
I- I- I-

999
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:17,200
I'm hungry. Me too.

1000
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:20,240
I also want to go eat.

1001
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:21,040
Yes, yes.

1002
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:21,760
Shouchang.

1003
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:24,400
Everyone's hungry. Everyone's hungry.

1004
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,240
Mr. Cai, can't I tell the truth?

1005
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:28,080
I just gestured to you, and you-

1006
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:29,600
Alright. Alright.

1007
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:30,480
Come on.

1008
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:32,560
I'll take you to the scholar's residence for dinner.

1009
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:33,680
Come on, my treat.

1010
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:34,880
You don't know.

1011
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:36,240
All countries are good.
